-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Sep 05, 2014 06:22AM EDT
-- None



Sept 5 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1020 GMT on Friday:

** New Zealand's packaging firm Reynolds has selected several private equity groups but no peers to participate in the second round of bidding for its Swiss subsidiary SIG Combibloc, several people familiar with the deal told Reuters. [ID:nL5N0R54RU]   ** Japan's Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp said it has agreed to raise its stake in Hong Kong's Bank of East Asia Ltd <0023.HK> to 17.5 percent from the current 9.6 percent in a deal worth $950 million. SMBC is core banking unit of Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc <8316.T>.[ID:nL3N0R633S]  ** Portugal's state holding company Parpublica has sold a 31.5 percent stake in postal firm CTT <CTT.LS> in the second and last stage of its privatization at 7.25 euros a share, raising 343 million euros ($443.7 million), Parpublica said. [ID:nL5N0R60UI]  ** Macquarie Group Ltd's <MQG.AX> Mexican real investment trust could raise most of the $415 million in a stock offering planned for this month from foreign investors, a sign that appetite for property assets in the country is swelling, two sources with direct knowledge of the transaction said. [ID:nL1N0R537M]  ** Atlas Mara Co-Nvest Ltd <ATMA.L>, the African investment vehicle of former Barclays boss Bob Diamond, said it had increased its stake in Union Bank of Nigeria Plc <UBN.LG> to almost 30 percent for $270 million. [ID:nL5N0R60KD]  ** German airport operator Fraport AG <FRAG.DE> has reached a deal to buy a 75.5 percent stake in Ljubljana airport <ARPO.LJ> as it seeks to expand its international reach. Fraport said the purchase price was 177.1 million euros and that it would make an offer to buy the rest. [ID:nWEA00F9N]  ** Europe's second-biggest insurer Axa SA <AXAF.PA> has offered between 500 million and 600 million zlotys ($154 million-$185 million) for the insurance arm of Poland's mBank SA <MBK.WA>, daily Puls Biznesu reported on Friday. [ID:nL5N0R60JP]  ** South Korea's Hyundai Green Food Co Ltd <005440.KS> said it has decided not to follow through with a planned $147 million acquisition of WiniaMando Inc as future growth for the kimchi refrigerator maker appeared limited. [ID:nL3N0R600C]  ** Financial data and news provider Bloomberg LP sold its Bloomberg Sports analysis division to data firm STATS LLC, the companies said on Thursday, marking the end of Bloomberg's four-year foray into the world of athletic number crunching. The companies declined to comment on terms, but a source close to the deal said the price was between $15 million and $20 million. [ID:nL1N0R5217]  ** Italy's biggest utility Enel SpA <ENEI.MI> will decide what to do with its stake in Spanish utility Endesa SA <ELE.MC> in the next 30 days and delisting the unit is one of the options, the group's CEO said on Friday. [ID:nL5N0R6138]  ** Brambles Ltd <BXB.AX>, the world's largest supplier of pallets, said on Friday it had signed a five-year agreement with Cathay Pacific Airways Ltd <0293.HK> to supply and manage containers and pallet accessories. [ID:nL3N0R55YU]  ** Russian tycoon Gennady Timchenko has cut his stake in petrochemical company Sibur, the firm said. Sibur did not disclose the price. [ID:nL5N0R609C]